name: Living Beyond Breast Cancer
description:
Living Beyond Breast Cancer is a national nonprofit organization that seeks to create a world that understands there is more than one way to have breast cancer. To fulfill our mission of providing trusted information and a community of support, we offer on-demand emotional, practical, and evidence-based content that is meaningful to those newly diagnosed, in treatment, post-treatment, and living with metastatic disease.

For 30 years, Living Beyond Breast Cancer has imparted wisdom and connection via conferences, events, a peer-to-peer helpline, and more. Today, we remain committed to creating a culture of acceptance‚Äîwhere sharing the diversity of the lived experience of breast cancer fosters self-advocacy and hope.

Learn more at LBBC.ORG.

ETHIOPIA NEGE is a web resource of up to date news on Ethiopia. Its aim is to inform visitors on current affairs and scholarly presentations regarding social, economic and political issues that affect Ethiopia and her people.

Ethiopia Nege is also a portal for the dissemination of Ethiopian culture as it pertains to her religious belief systems as well as the developments in the secular sectors. The arts in cinema, music, poetry, painting and literary presentations can found in video, written and audio formats.

This is not just a travel vlog, this is life in East Africa, Ethiopia Life blog; I created this channel to share, celebrate and highlight what life is like here in the beautifully diverse, ancient custom-filled and culturally rich land. Join me on my journeys and adventures across this epic destination on the road less traveled. I am Jai Lennox and I have LOVED Ethiopia ever since I visited over 10 years ago and never left.

To share my love of Ethiopia with the world.
To celebrate the vast diversity across Ethiopia whilst at the same time highlighting the vast oneness of all its beautiful cultures.
To challenge and reframe the rhetoric of Ethiopia and Africa as a whole.

name: Selah Ethiopia
description:
Selah serves Ethiopian women in and outside of Ethiopia by working to increase Biblical literacy and thereby encouraging and equipping for vulnerable, thought-provoking conversations around the Gospel of Jesus Christ, the mission of the Church, and the life of a Christian. Selah, a phrase mentioned in the Bible a handful of times, prompts the reader to stop and reflect. The Psalmist reminds us there is a relationship between praise, worship, and being reflective and still before the Lord. Our aim is to foster a sense of community by allowing a space for deeper and authentic reflection rooted in the Word of God. 

Selah hosts resources including articles, reflections, Bible studies, and devotionals in various media. The purpose of each and every content is to deepen our understanding of our faith and to encourage women to live every day with eternity in mind.

name: AradaTube Amharic
description:
This YouTube channel is dedicated to sharing my experience and knowledge in the field of information technology with my fellow countrymen. Information technology has become an integral part of our daily lives, and it has transformed the way we live and work. As technology continues to advance, we are discovering new ways to integrate it into our daily routines.

The primary objective of this channel is to help individuals overcome their daily IT challenges. I will be sharing tips, tricks, and advice on how to resolve common IT-related issues that we face in our daily lives. Additionally, I hope to inspire and encourage the youth to pursue a career in the IT industry.

Join me on this journey as we explore the exciting world of information technology together. I welcome your questions, requests, and comments, and I will do my best to respond to them in a timely manner.

Thank you for your interest, and let's learn and grow together in the world of IT.

name: Psych in Amharic with Tamiru Delelegn
description: I was born and grew up in eastern Ethiopia, Jijiga town. Got my B.Edand M.Ed in Pedagogical Sciences and Educational Psychology respectively from Bahir Dar university. I have been serving in BDU for the past 16 years. Teaching in class and surfing in the library have been the happiest settings of my life for many years. I was particularly "addicted" to teaching Personality Psychology. Got special interest for Ethiopian history too. I enjoy and value volunteering and working with students. "Memories of Ethiopia" is a testimonial video archive depicting the lives of Jews in Ethiopia. It is aimed at preserving their cultural and historical heritage and making it accessible to present and future generations.  
 
The video archive includes in-depth testimonials and life stories of one hundred interviewees from twelve districts in Ethiopia. More than 175 hours of video recordings provide insight into the extraordinary lives of the Beta Israel in Ethiopia.

name: Ethiopiawinet Dance crew
description: Welcome to the official channel of ethiopiawinet dance crew The 6-member Ethiopiawinet Cultural Dance Crew is one of the most popular dance groups in Ethiopia. Since their founding in 2009, they have won numerous national dance competitions including Balgeru Idol and performed in many music videos with popular Ethiopian singers. Ethiopiawinet specializes in traditional music and dances from Ethiopia, Eritrea, and across East Africa. Incorporating songs, dance, drumming and theatre, the group aspires to promote Ethiopian dance art and culture around the world. Exposed to diverse global dance forms, Ethiopiawinet remains grounded in deep and rich Ethiopian dance heritage and committed to sharing our heritage and its creative potential on world stages.

name: Jimma Tube
description:
CLICK HERE: 
#https://cutt.ly/ZrDlH47

Jimma is one of the zones of the Ethiopian Region of Oromia. Jimma is named for the former Kingdom of Jimma, which was absorbed into the former province of Kaffa in 1932. Jimma is bordered on the south by the Southern Nations, Nationalities and Peoples Region, the northwest by Illubabor, on the north by Misraq Welega, and on the northeast by Mirab Shewa; part of the boundary with Misraq Shewa is defined by the Gibe River. The highest point in this zone is Mount Maigudo (2,386 m). Towns and cities in Jimma include Agaro, Genet and Saqqa. The town of Jimma was separated from Jimma Zone and is a special zone now.

name: HuletLingo
description:
Hello! Welcome to HuletLingo! My name is Mel, and I'm an avid bookworm passionate about teaching Amharic and introducing Ethiopian culture to people like you! I started this channel with the idea of offering easy-to-follow videos for all Amharic learners, so whether you're a proficient Amharic speaker or a beginner, my videos have you covered! I create videos on various topics, from pronunciation to helpful conversation starters and daily conversations you might have with people. 
If you are like me, you're tired of seeing videos that are hard to follow and add unnecessary complexity to even the most straightforward concepts. If your goal is to introduce yourself in Amharic, and that should be what you should learn, not superfluous grammar rules. Plain and simple is sometimes the best route, and I've got you covered. Join me and subscribe for an immersive learning experience and take your skills to the next level!
If you need anything, I'll be happy to help if I can.

With Love, 
Mel

name: Think in Amharic
description:
Welcome to my channel! 

Think in Amharic is a YouTube channel where I teach basic Amharic. Anyone interested to learn Amharic is welcome. 

Learning a new language is a process, & it should be a fun journey.
So don't beat yourself up! 
To learn Amharic in a short time, teach yourself to think in Amharic.
Most foreigners, think in their native language first, then go on to translate what they want to say in Amharic. The problem is that the sentence structures are different in your language. That's the slowest way you can take to achieve Amharic fluency.

Start simple. Take baby steps. Stay consistent. Do not give up!



I upload 3 videos every week, please subscribe so you won't miss a lesson.
 
#learnamharic #learnamharicwithme #learnbasicamharic #amhariclanguage 
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~















#amhariclesson #amhariclessons #basicamhariclessons #basicamhariclanguage #conversationalamharic #amharicletterswithsamesound #learnamhariconline

When WE(BLACK GODDESS/GODS) wake up to who WE ARE, break the chains of mental slavery, reclaim OURistory, and take back what has been STOLEN from US, then will WE asend back to OUR RIGHTFUL PLACE ON THE THRONE OF THE UNIVERSE!!!!

OLODUMARE: "The HIGHEST, The ALMIGHTY, The I AM that I AM, The OM, The CREATOR and SOURCE of all that is!!!!" ...literal Yoruba definition is: "The Highest, the Most Exalted One from who I emanated and to whom I must return!"

AMEN-RA: 'LIGHT shinning out of COMPLETE(PERFECT) BLACKNESS!"


AUSET: "The BLACKNESS of the vast un-manifest regions of existence!" (Female aspect of AMEN-RA)

AUSAR: "Lord of the PERFECT BLACK!!" (Male aspect of AMEN-RA)

HERU: "The union between AUSAR and AUSET! The union between SPIRIT and CREATION! GOD "made flesh", the "INCARNATION"! HERU is the "MANIFESTATION" of the GODDESS/GOD on earth! HERU is the "BLACK  WOMAN/MAN, GODDESS/GODS  on earth"!!!



ODUDUWA: "Exalted, Self Existent, BLACK ONE"

YAHOUSHUA: "Original name of Jesus"

*Note: Oduduwa is the original Pre-Kemetian KRST (Christ) figure, founder of Ile Ife (The Lost City of Atlantis) later identified as SUT, Tar, Ptah, Ausar, Heru, Krishna, Brahma, Shiva, Vishnu, Yahoushua, etc.
